Distribution and habitat. Known only from the type locality, Tuisi River, a tributary of Kaladan River of Mizoram (
Fig. 3
). It is found in moderate to fast flowing water with sparse vegetation and a substrate of pebbles, sand, gravel and small boulders. The Kaladan River, locally known as the Chhimtuipui, originates from the Chin Hills of Myanmar and flows through the southern part of Mizoram, India , and empties into the Bay of Bengal near Sittwe in Myanmar . It is located between the Ganges-Brahmaputra and the Ann Chaung drainage on the western slope of the RakhineYoma Mountain Range, Myanmar .
